                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.472,
                                "byte_start": 91806,
                                "byte_stop": 129736,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 91-1950, American Dredging Company against Miller will be announced by Justice Scalia."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.472,
                        "stop": 200.464,
                        "byte_start": 129736,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15049,
                            "name": "Antonin Scalia",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/antonin_scalia",
                            "last_name": "Scalia",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2693,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 528094800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2693"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32678,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 58944,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/antonin_scalia_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 10699,
                            "identifier": "antonin_scalia"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.472,
                                "stop": 14.277,
                                "byte_start": 129736,
                                "byte_stop": 148962,
                                "text": "This case is here on certiorari from the Supreme Court of Louisiana."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.277,
                                "stop": 31.074,
                                "byte_start": 148962,
                                "byte_stop": 216149,
                                "text": "The respondent, William Robert Miller, was injured while working as a seaman board a tug operating on the Delaware River and owned by the petitioner, American Dredging Company, a Pennsylvania Corporation with its principal place of business in New Jersey."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 31.074,
                                "stop": 50.014,
                                "byte_start": 216149,
                                "byte_stop": 291904,
                                "text": "After returning home to Mississippi, Miller brought this action for damages under what is called the savings to suitors clause of the United States Code, 28 U.S.C. Section 1333(1), and under the Jones Act which is 46 U.S.C. App. Section 688."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.014,
                                "stop": 59.31,
                                "byte_start": 291904,
                                "byte_stop": 329102,
                                "text": "He brought that suit in the Civil District Court, the State District Court, for Orleans, Louisiana."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.31,
                                "stop": 73.29,
                                "byte_start": 329102,
                                "byte_stop": 385004,
                                "text": "That court, however, granted American Dredging\u0027s motion to dismiss based on the doctrine of forum non conveniens under which a court may decline to exercise jurisdiction if a more appropriate forum exists."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 73.29,
                                "stop": 93.054,
                                "byte_start": 385004,
                                "byte_stop": 464103,
                                "text": "The District Court concluded that federal maritime law which governs the merits of Miller\u0027s claim required application of forum non conveniens not withstanding the fact that the Louisiana Code of Civil Procedure purports to render that doctrine unavailable in maritime cases brought in Louisiana State Courts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 93.054,
                                "stop": 103.264,
                                "byte_start": 464103,
                                "byte_stop": 504959,
                                "text": "The Supreme Court of Louisiana reversed holding that Louisiana\u0027s statutory prohibition of forum non conveniens is not preempted by federal maritime law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 103.264,
                                "stop": 106.714,
                                "byte_start": 504959,
                                "byte_stop": 518751,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari and now affirm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.714,
                                "stop": 113.905,
                                "byte_start": 518751,
                                "byte_stop": 547486,
                                "text": "In admiralty cases filed in a State Court, federal law does not preempt state law regarding the doctrine of forum non conveniens."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.905,
                                "stop": 130.228,
                                "byte_start": 547486,
                                "byte_stop": 612792,
                                "text": "We have long held that State Court\u0027s hearing admiralty cases may adapt such remedies as they see fit so long as those remedies do not materially prejudice what we have called characteristic features or interfere with the proper uniformity of admiralty law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.228,
                                "stop": 141.481,
                                "byte_start": 612792,
                                "byte_stop": 657827,
                                "text": "Because forum non conveniens did not originate in admiralty and is a doctrine of general application not limited to admiralty, we think it not a characteristic feature of admiralty law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 141.481,
                                "stop": 173.937,
                                "byte_start": 657827,
                                "byte_stop": 787604,
                                "text": "Moreover, application of forum non conveniens is not necessary to assure proper uniformity of admiralty law for two reasons: First, it is really a supervening venue rule procedural in nature rather than a substantive rule upon which maritime actors rely in making decisions about how to manage their business affairs; and secondly, it is unlikely to produce uniformed results anyway because the doctrine vests enormous discretion in the Trial Court and encompasses multifarious factors in its application."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 173.937,
                                "stop": 189.45,
                                "byte_start": 787604,
                                "byte_stop": 849670,
                                "text": "Our conclusion is confirmed by prior decisions under the Jones Act and the Federal Employers Liability Act which imply that federal venue rules including forum non conveniens are matters of judicial housekeeping prescribed only for the Federal Courts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 189.45,
                                "stop": 200.464,
                                "byte_start": 849670,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Souter has filed a concurring opinion; Justice Stevens has filed an opinion concurring in part and concurring in the judgment; Justice Kennedy has filed a dissenting opinion which is joined by Justice Thomas."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
